						<summary>

						<p>Sōmasundarēśvara temple, north base.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vikramachōḻa Year 6.</hi></p>						

						<p>The beginning of the inscription is lost and it is very much damaged.</p>						

						<p>It records a <hi rend="italic">nimandam</hi> (arrangement) made by the <hi rend="italic">ūr</hi> of Vayiramēghapuram in Tirunalūr-nāḍu to exempt from taxes some land in Eyilūr (in the temple ?). The <hi rend="italic">ūr</hi> seems to have undertaken to pay the concerned taxes themselves. </p>						

						</summary>
